76561198027378697,Recommended,488550,30568136,Posted: 17 March,all,Trent Stark,"If you like physics games, this is a very good physics game! The physics engine has a very realistic feel and it is smooth as well.If you're like me and you like cars, engines and mechanical engineering concepts, you'll probably enjoy this game as much as I have been. I tend to spend hours on one vehicle, tweaking suspension, frame size/weight/length/width, tires until it is just right. This game makes that kind of gameplay available.Where this game really shines for me is the suspension. I can't believe how amazing it looks and feels while going over bumps and taking sharp turns. The possibilities of suspensions you can make seem endless, and you're not even limited to just the shocks that are a provided part. You can even use frame parts with elasticity tweaks and come up with your own suspension designs, as you may see when checking out the workshop (which has many, awesome designs).I personally don't like shallow and arcade-style physics games that invovles vehicles. This one is the opposite.Now for some reality: It is early access. The game does feel a little empty after a while.A big one for many - it is not multiplayer. Not a big deal for me really but I know some may not prefer that.But, jets were just added! So one good thing about this game is that it is not done with additional content. So with that in mind, this is a good time waster. I'd say it's well worth the time I've put into it.Overall I give this game a thumbs up! For the price, it's definitely a good deal and plenty of enjoyment."
